    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 9 February 1539)</head>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <p>1. Oláh has his sympathy in his grief for his lost brother, and Nanninck
                            wants to console him, but he cannot even ease his own sadness. He is
                            sending this elegy for his consolation. 2. He has written him many times
                            already what he thinks of <hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> and <hi
                                rend="italic">Hungaria</hi>, he is not ashamed of his opinion,
                            unless it seems spiteful.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Reverendo domino Nicolao Olaho, thesaurario Albensi, archidiacono
                    Strigoniensi, serenissimi Ferdinandi Romanorum regis atc. ac Mariae reginae a
                    secretis et consiliis, Petrus Nannius salutem dicit.</p>
                <p>[1.] Acerbissimos tuos luctus de amicissimo fratre<note type="critic"
                        >Máté Oláh died in 1536, see Oláh’s epitaphs on his brother’s death: <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 419–421; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 38–40; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 342
                        –344. Oláh’s friends sent a heap of condolences, elegies, and epitaphs from
                        the Netherlands to lessen his grief, which Nanninck published in print, see
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 417; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Tournoy</hi> 2006, 135–139. See the manuscripts: ELTE EK H 46, fol.
                        31–43.</note> non lacrimis tantummodo, sed gravi aegritudine animi
                    prosequor, et ex laboribus adversae valetudinis, qua nunc affligor, nihil tam
                    triste sentio, quam cruciatus istius maeroris. Et ut libenter studium consolandi
                    prae me ferrem (tametsi tua sapientia et animi fortitudo istiusmodi adminiculis
                    non egeat), ita ipse vix <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><choice>
                                <orig>inven<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>inven<corr>io</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">invenio</rdg>
                    </app>, quo maestitiam meam commitigem. Quamobrem, ut in te consolando nonnihil
                    ipse acquiescerem, carmen hoc elegiacum super consolationes fraternae mortis,
                    quod ad te mitto, condidi, qualecumque ab animo ita misere afflicto exprimere
                    potui.</p>
                <p>[Nunc utinam Pyliae…]<note type="critic">See <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Tournoy</hi> 2006, 150–151.</note></p>
                <pb/>
                <p>[2.] De <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><del corresp="Olahus">tua</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">tuo</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">tuo</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> et Hungariae descriptione<note type="critic">I.e.
                            <hi rend="italic">Hungaria</hi>.</note> quid sentiam, iam saepius
                    litteris meis testatus sum. Cuius me iudicii nunquam paenitebit, nisi quod
                    malignius videor et nimis parce rei laudatissimae laudes impertiisse. Olim
                    carmine testabimur, quantus mihi videare. Plura scriberem, sed doloribus morbi
                    huius ita excrucior, ut vix compos <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><choice>
                                <orig>menti<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>menti<corr>s</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">menti</rdg>
                    </app> sim.</p>
                <p>Vale, Unicum <quote>Praesidium Meum!</quote><note type="quote">Cf. Hor.
                            <hi rend="italic">Carm</hi>. I,I,2.</note><note type="critic">See Ep.
                        598. Cap. 3.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15371222_1</ref></p>
                <p><placeName>Lovanii</placeName>, nona <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"><choice>
                                <orig>Februar<gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                                <supplied>Februar<corr>ii</corr></supplied>
                            </choice></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">Februarii</rdg>
                    </app> anno MDXXXIX.</p>
            </div>
